# OWASP Security Shepherd & Burp Suite on WSL: Complete Deployment Guide

This document outlines the complete setup from scratch, including handling the dynamic installation authentication tokens, standard credentials, database links, and solving your target modules.

---

## Part 1: Environment Prerequisites & Java Configuration

Ubuntu 24.04 defaults to Java 21, but Security Shepherd requires **Java 17 (OpenJDK 17)** to compile the web application component successfully.

### Step 1: Install System Dependencies

Open your WSL terminal and execute the following to update your system and install necessary packages (avoiding conflicting legacy Docker tools):

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y git maven openjdk-17-jdk docker-compose-plugin

```

### Step 2: Force the Java 17 Compiler Environment

To prevent the `Fatal error compiling: error: release version 17 not supported` Maven error, explicitly configure your terminal session paths to link directly to Java 17:

```bash
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH

```

> 🔍 **Verify:** Run `java -version` and `javac -version` to confirm that **17.x.x** is displayed before executing the build engine.

